## 4-Tier FLUX ISA — PUBLISHED TO crates.io

The constraint VM now spans from microcontroller to data center:

### flux-isa-mini v0.1.0 ✅ PUBLISHED crates.io
- no_std, zero allocation, 256-byte stack, 24-byte instructions
- Runs on ARM Cortex-M0+/M3/M4 (8KB SRAM)
- 21 opcodes, sonar bounds checking, 2-byte wire format
- Sensor gateway: validate raw readings before forwarding
- `cargo install flux-isa-mini`

### flux-isa-std v0.1.0 ✅ PUBLISHED crates.io
- Full std Rust, 37 opcodes, heap allocation, CLI tool
- File persistence, JSON serialization, quality gate
- Mackenzie 1981 + Francois-Garrison 1982 sonar physics
- RPi/BeagleBone tier: `flux run`, `flux validate`, `flux disassemble`
- `cargo install flux-isa-std`

### flux-isa-edge v0.1.0 ✅ PUBLISHED crates.io
- Async tokio, Axum HTTP+WebSocket, PLATO sync with offline mode
- Sensor pipelines with backpressure, configurable batch
- 25/25 tests passing
- Jetson Xavier NX tier: real-time constraint validation
- `cargo install flux-isa-edge`

### flux-isa-thor v0.1.0 🔨 BUILDING NOW
- CUDA FFI, fleet coordination, 43 opcodes (35 base + 8 Thor extensions)
- Batch CSP solving on GPU, 5-stage pipeline (INGEST→VALIDATE→COMPILE→EXECUTE→COMMIT)
- gRPC fleet comms, Prometheus metrics
- Jetson Thor / AGX Orin / data center GPU tier

